## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design multisource joins with simple, robust windowing and per-topic state management in KCNA. It exercises offset handling, at-least-once guarantees, and failure/restart semantics without requiring complex infrastructure.

## Key Concepts
- Per-topic buffering keyed by orderId
- Windowed join with 45s bound
- Atomic offset commits on emission
- Handling of partials and expirations

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudocode sketch
class Joiner {
  constructor(windowMs) { this.window = windowMs; this.buffers = new Map(); }
  onMessage(topic, msg, ts) {
    const key = msg.orderId;
    const bucket = this.buffers.get(key) || {orders: null, payments: null, shipments: null, times: []};
    bucket[topic] = msg;
    bucket.times.push(ts);
    if (bucket.orders && bucket.payments && bucket.shipments) {
      const w = Math.max(...bucket.times) - Math.min(...bucket.times);
      if (w <= this.window) this.emit(key, bucket);
    }
    this.buffers.set(key, bucket);
  }
  emit(key, bucket) {
    // publish to fulfillments and commit offsets for involved messages
    // prune buffers after emit
  }
}
```

