## Why This Is Asked
This question assesses your understanding of windowed joins, late-data handling, and stateful stream processing in Kafka Confluent ecosystem.

## Key Concepts
- **Windowed Joins**: Per-user 15-second tumbling windows with join semantics between click and purchase events
- **Late Data Tolerance**: 20-second watermark allowance for out-of-order event processing
- **State Management**: Per-user window state with cleanup logic for expired windows
- **Delivery Semantics**: At-least-once guarantees with offset preservation
- **Canary Testing**: Design patterns for validating out-of-order input handling

## Code Example
```javascript
class WindowedJoinProcessor {
  constructor(options = {}) {
    this.joinWindowMs = options.joinWindowMs || 15000;
    this.lateThresholdMs = options.lateThresholdMs || 20000;
    this.state = new Map(); // userId -> { windows: Map<windowKey, WindowState> }
  }

  onMessage(topic, msg, offset) {
    const key = JSON.parse(msg.key);
    const value = JSON.parse(msg.value);
    const watermark = Date.now() - this.lateThresholdMs;

    if (value.ts < watermark) return; // discard late data

    const windowKey = this.getWindowKey(value.ts);
    this.updateState(topic, key.userId, windowKey, value, offset);
    this.emitIfWindowComplete(key.userId, windowKey);
  }

  getWindowKey(timestamp) {
    return Math.floor(timestamp / this.joinWindowMs) * this.joinWindowMs;
  }

  updateState(topic, userId, windowKey, value, offset) {
    // maintain per-user, per-window state with latest offset
  }

  emitIfWindowComplete(userId, windowKey) {
    // emit aggregated result to 'user_activity' topic
  }
}
```

## API Hooks Required
- `onMessage(topic, msg, offset)` - ingress hook for processing incoming events
