**Solution Overview:**
Buffer messages per partition within a 5-second window. When the window closes, emit the batch to the sink and commit offsets atomically. Use per-partition in-memory buffers backed by a durable write-ahead log (WAL) to survive crashes. Ensure at-least-once delivery with deduplication by tracking processed message IDs and making the sink idempotent.

**API Design:**
- `onMessage(msg, partition)`: Buffers incoming messages per partition with timestamp
- `onBatchComplete(batch, partition)`: Callback invoked after successful batch emission to sink; triggers offset commit
- `commitOffsets(partition, offset)`: Atomically commits offsets to Kafka after successful sink write

**Batching Strategy:**
- Per-partition buffers maintain message ordering within each partition
- Timer resets after each batch window closes
- Offsets are committed only after the sink confirms receipt
- In-memory buffer combined with a WAL provides crash recovery capability

**Canary Test:**
Inject test messages into the stream, terminate the process mid-batch, then restart and verify that no messages are duplicated or lost.

**Code Example:**
```javascript
class KCNABatcher {
  constructor(windowMs = 5000) {
    this.buffers = new Map();
    this.timers = new Map();
    this.windowMs = windowMs;
    this.processedIds = new Set();
  }

  onMessage(msg, partition) {
    if (!this.buffers.has(partition)) {
      this.buffers.set(partition, []);
    }
    this.buffers.get(partition).push(msg);
    this.startWindowTimer(partition);
  }

  startWindowTimer(partition) {
    if (this.timers.has(partition)) return;
    this.timers.set(partition, setTimeout(() => {
      this.flush(partition);
    }, this.windowMs));
  }

  async flush(partition) {
    const batch = this.buffers.get(partition);
    if (!batch?.length) return;

    const unprocessed = batch.filter(m => !this.processedIds.has(m.id));
    if (unprocessed.length === 0) return;

    await this.onBatchComplete(unprocessed, partition);
    await this.commitOffsets(partition, batch[batch.length - 1].offset + 1);

    unprocessed.forEach(m => this.processedIds.add(m.id));
    this.buffers.set(partition, []);
    this.timers.delete(partition);
  }

  async onBatchComplete(batch, partition) {
    await sink.write(batch);
  }

  async commitOffsets(partition, offset) {
    await consumer.commit({ topic: 'events', partition, offset });
  }
}
```

**Crash Recovery:**
- Persist the batch to a local WAL before processing
- On restart, read the WAL and reprocess any uncommitted batches
- Deduplicate using message ID tracking to prevent duplicate emission

**At-Least-Once + Deduplication:**
- Commit offsets only after the sink write succeeds
- Store processed message IDs in a durable store
- Check message ID before emitting to prevent duplicates

